capstone.element

Class Element

  • java.lang.Object
    • capstone.element.Element
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DynamicObstacle, Entrance, Exit, Key, MysteryBox, Player, StaticObstacle, Wall

    public abstract class Element
extends java.lang.Object
    The base-class for all renderable elements of the game. Defines some base operations and attributes all elements have in common. All elements are defined by a point on the screen, a kind enum member to cheat the type-system as well as a Representation object used to render the element onto the screen. All elements can be rendered onto a screen and "unrendered" off it.

      • render

        public void render(com.googlecode.lanterna.screen.Screen screen,
                   Region relativeTo)
        Renders the Element onto the screen, relativeTo the region. The relativeTo Region is necessary because the points of Elements are always absolute with respected to the level, while they must be relative to the Terminal when (un)rendered. Thus the relativeTo Region is first "subtracted" from the Point. The relativeTo Region must be the Region the Element is contained in.
        Parameters:
        screen - The Screen to render the Element onto.
        relativeTo - The Region containing the Element.

      • unrender

        public void unrender(com.googlecode.lanterna.screen.Screen screen,
                     Region relativeTo)
        Unrenders the Element onto the screen, relativeTo the region. The relativeTo Region is necessary because the points of Elements are always absolute with respected to the level, while they must be relative to the Terminal when (un)rendered. Thus the relativeTo Region is first "subtracted" from the Point. The relativeTo Region must be the Region the Element is contained in.
        Parameters:
        screen - The Screen to unrender the Element from.
        relativeTo - The Region containing the Element.

      • _render

        protected void _render(com.googlecode.lanterna.screen.Screen screen,
                       Region relativeTo,
                       com.googlecode.lanterna.screen.ScreenCharacterStyle... styles)
        Renders the Element onto the Screen relative to the Region, and also applying the given styles. This method can be used by subclasses that wish to add some styles to the rendering of the Elements of their kind. The default implementation of render() in Element calls this method with no styles.
        Parameters:
        screen - The Screen to render Elements onto.
        relativeTo - The Region containing the Element.
        styles - The array of ScreenCharacterStyles to apply.
